      • auxFlow

        private double auxFlow
        Auxiliary flow used in equilibrium calculations

      • length

        double length
        Total length of this path. This usually does not change, as opposed to the travel time, which varies with network conditions.

      • genCost

        public double genCost
        Generalised cost on path ("actual" cost), but without path size correction term. Generally, this should be the linear, additive part of the deterministic utility, so that it can be defined as the sum of generalized cost on the edges of the path.

      • enumeratorInProbabilityExpression

        public double enumeratorInProbabilityExpression

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Path o)
        The natural ordering of paths uses their generalized cost. This make it possible to sort a list of paths using Collections.sort(java.util.List).
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Path>

      • computeEnumeratorInProbabilityExpression

        public double computeEnumeratorInProbabilityExpression(RouteChoiceModel rcm)
        Computes the enumerator in the probability expression of the route choice model (most often simply a RUM) using the route choice model's own method of the same name.
        Parameters:
        rcm - the route choice model that will determine the value to return
        Returns:
        a number which corresponds for e.g. the MNL to exp(-theta*V).
        See Also:
        RouteChoiceModel.computeEnumeratorInProbabilityExpression(Path)

      • computeTransformedCost

        public double computeTransformedCost(RouteChoiceModel rcm)
        Calculate the transformed cost of this path. In general, it is equal to the flow on the route divided by the value returned by computeEnumeratorInProbabilityExpression(RouteChoiceModel), but if the flow on the route is 0, 0 is return before evaluating the latter to save some computation time.
        Parameters:
        rcm - the route choice model to determine the transformed cost to return
        Returns:
        the transformed cost of the route according to the route choice model
